review_text:
I have a very long review for people who are worried about spending money or worried about the dress. I was very nervous myself and though the other reviews helped, I still didn't feel very confident about my purchase. I can tell you now that I have no regrets and absolute trust in this company. This dress is absolutely stunning and I will buy from them again.

Before I purchased:
I was very skeptical. I don't like spending that much money, especially on a dress online. I have ordered things from china before and they always came back in poor quality. I have seen many variations of this dress online and all of them ended up being very cheep like. I did not want to end up buying something I would regret later. My senior prom was coming up FAST. I had 3 weeks. The estimated tracking said it would arrive sometime a month later, but after an E Mail to the seller, I was assured the dress would be here ASAP.

After the purchase:
The dress came in 10 days. I was so happy! The colors were matching beautifully. Yes the skirt is a little darker than the top, but that's because it has a thin fabric overlaying the original color. I think it looks prettier that way. The sizing is true! I got one a little bigger just in case and found out I would have been just fine ordering a size smaller. The dress is very flat. You NEED a petticoat for it to look correct! I got one off of
E Bay for $25 and it looked like it was meant to be.

Possible adjustments:
*I could not for the life of me figure out why the front of the dress was way longer than the back! I was stepping on my dress the first few days I had it till I decided to hem it up. But my theory is that its a "princess" dress and princesses carry the fronts when they walk around. TADA
*The color of the dress is a hard color to match if you're trying to buy fabric for sleeves! I ended up buying a slightly lighter fabric with a dark thin fabric to go over it. it looked a lot like the skirt so it matched nicely!
*Some of the beading was coming undone so I hand stitched a few things a little tighter and they were good as new again

Prom night:
We went to dinner first at a local dinner and were stopped by many guests. I was told by many people that the dress was stunning and the best of the group. A little girl even asked to take a picture with the "Princess". I also received many complements at the dance. Everyone was surprised I had ordered it online for the price that it was. It could easily be a $300 dress. Im not kidding, it is that beautiful. I actually won prom queen and best dress that night. It was all amazing.

In closing:
I have never been so happy with a dress in my life till now. Its not only something that made my night enchanting, but its something I can hold for my future daughters and their proms. I am very happy with the sellers and I have absolute trust in their company. I will buy from them again :) If you are skeptical and a worrier like I am, don't be afraid to buy this dress. Its worth every penny.

review_text:
It can be difficult to purchase clothing online so here's my take on this dress. The color was not as pictured. I ordered the blue, expecting a more navy, as shown. The dress was a brighter blue but not like royal blue. The picture I attached was taken in natural light.
The fit was the biggest problem. I wear a size 10, sometimes 12, so ordered two sizes up as recommended by other reviewers. The length was a bit too long, the sleeves were so tight I was afraid I was going to rip it as I took it off, it was too tight in the bust and the waist was too loose. I'm not unusually shaped or anything so I don't know what size I would actually wear. I initially figured I would just alter it but then decided the color wasn't what I really wanted, so back it goes.
The fabric was soft and flowed nicely. The sequins were attached well and the overall sewing was good.

review_text: It is supposed to fit loose in the 1920's style but after reading reviews my daughter ordered a small rather than her usual medium. There is a (separate) slip liner which is definitely needed since the dress fabric is flimsy. Held up okay so far (hand washed cold and it hang dries fast). She maybe could have got away with an XS but then the liner would have been way too tight. (So, if you want a size that's not super baggy, you might have to provide your own slip underneath.) She got the design with little black and salmon color pattern and it is reminiscent of the times. Some of the patterns/colors shown don't really represent 1920's fashion so she wanted to be as close as possible for her event. Got a little felt cloche style hat on Amazon also so she was happy with the overall look.

review_text: I am 5'4" and 170 lbs, with big shoulders, chest, waist, & hips.  I ordered this in size 14 and size 16.  The 14 fit well, so I did not try on the 16.  This one is nice but the one I *loved* on me was "[[ASIN:B06Y3W1ZY5 R&M Richards Women's 2 Piece Mesh Panel Beaded Neck Jacket Dress, Slate, 14]]". I am attaching a picture that shows both; this one is on the left.  I felt like this one made me look bigger and the other outfit made me look smaller.  If you are taller than I am, then this dress is slightly longer as you can see from the picture. This one is also fully lined and the sparkly bit is a separate layer of fabric on the outside.  If you are tall and have more feminine shoulders and are less busty than I, then this might work better because it has shoulder pads and a good bit of fabric draping the front.  I feel like both of these items look better with the jacket on, which is how they are meant to be worn.  I would recommend either one, and would certainly look at R&M Richards again the next time I am buying a dress for a festive occasion.

review_text: It's more of a costume than a dress, but for the price I paid, it was a good deal.  My daughter wore the white version to a fancy Girl Scout "Soiree en Blanc" event wearing it, and she received many compliments. She wanted something that was different from a standard girls' party dress, and with a scarf and faux pearls for accessories, she looked adorable.  She's a little over 5 feet tall and 110 pounds, and it fit perfectly.  Be aware that the back has neither fringe nor sequins and is quite sheer.  You definitely want to wear a slip underneath--without one, you can see underwear from the back, even under opaque tights.  (In the photo I took, it looks shorter than it actually was--it hit right above the knee. But you can see that it's fun to shimmy with the fringe.)

review_text:
Don't get me wrong. I love this dress. It's so soft and comfy and so versatile you can dress it up or down to wear anyplace. Bought every color. Sadly, had to down it one star because A. The dark blue arrived with a noticeable hole in the front, near the neckline. I'm returning it for an exchange B. The neckline and shoulders fit a little oddly. If you are broad shouldered it shouldn't be a problem. If, like me, you have little bird shoulders you will find they tend to pucker a bit at the shoulder seam. C. If you're very busty buy the next larger size. Mine tends to stretch a little tight across my bust. I still like it and will still wear it.

All told, they are the perfect house dress. When I wear them outside I put a cardi or vest over it to conceal the peculiar shoulders.

review_text: My female barbershop quartet wore these dresses for our competitions and we received many, many compliments on how the dress shows on stage. We ordered sizes S, L, XL, and XXL. Due to the stretch material underneath, these dresses are forgiving should one gain a little weight. The XXL's fringe in the bust area was too short...about 1/2 inch of under fabric was exposed. Even contacted the manufacturer about this and their suggestion was to re-order. I ended up buying at least 4 dresses to see if there were any that had the same length fringe, but ended up having a friend alter the dress for me. She even removed the side zipper as I never used it. Length alterations was easy -- simply cut off the bottom row. As you can see from the pic, we won our regional competition...certainly a very lucky dress!

review_text:
I'm a petite woman. I'm 5'2" and weigh about 135 pounds. This dress fits me very well. However, I read other reviews that were not impressed with the one size fit. I can certainly say that if you're much bigger than I am, the top of the dress, specifically the neck and arm holes, are probably going to be a bit tight. However, if you're a petite woman, you're going to LOVE this dress. It's gorgeous. I chose the red wine color and the color is perfect. The dress has a beautiful flow and the belt at the waist allows it to accentuate your best features while hiding the areas that you may be more self conscious about. I'm so happy with this dress. Not only is it beautiful, but it's comfortable too.
This dress is a great piece to add to your wardrobe, because it's very versatile. I purchased it to wear to a spring wedding, but it would be ideal to bring on vacation or wear to a company party. With the right hair and accessories, this dress can easily go from the beach to evening wear. I'm very happy with this purchase and the quality of the dress.

*I received this dress at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest review, and that is exactly what this is - my HONEST opinion.

That being said, there are some definite fit issues with this dress. I ordered a size M to fit my largest measurement and make sure that no buttons pulled across the chest, but the sleeves are extremely baggy. It‚Äôs not too bad if you roll up the sleeves but looks a little dumpy otherwise. I also this there should be two pockets on the chest instead of one for better symmetry. Finally, I usually wear this dress with a wider belt because I think that looks better on me personally.

All in all it‚Äôs very cozy and I like the dress.
